  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>For five-star business events in Thailand, Le Meridien Bangkok offers stylish meeting rooms, two VIP boardrooms and a private foyer, perfect for intimate corporate and social functions. The entire sixth floor of the hotel is dedicated to pursuing a unique luxury lifestyle experience, including SPA inspired by the rich tradition of European spas, a Technogym-equipped fitness centre featuring upbeat urban music and an outdoor pool to chill out with cool drinks and cocktails, while looking out over busy Bangkok below. This five star hotel is the another good choice for guests who want to stay with luxury class accommodation and in the center of Bangkok.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>Hotel is just a short walk from shopping and dining on Silom Road and the excitement of the Patpong Night Market. Jim Thompson House and Museum, Siam Paragon Shopping Centre, Suan Lumpini Night Bazaar, Hua Lamphong Temple and Chinatown are just a short ride away by subway - sam yan station or sky train -Saladaeng.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>All rooms are deluxe and of a very high standard and are very large at 45 square metres. Bathrooms are of an equally high standard with a large separate shower cubicle and large tubs. Amenities provided are of the usual high standard.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>The hotel is a high building with 24 storeys into skyline, towering in contemporary five-star luxury at the head of the pulsating Silom commercial district.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>Restaurant which is now available serving international cuisines, Bamboo Chic Bar present a variety of snacks, sandwiches and delicatessen in a contemporary lounge setting. The Latest Recipe, an international a la carte menu and buffet with "live" cooking stations where fresh ingredients are cooked-to-order. Or relaxing with wireless high-speed Internet access overlooking Bangkok's Surawong Road at Tempo.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The lobby, guest's senses are stimulated by Le Meridien's signature "Le Labo" scent, "Sony BMG" unique sound and the creative use of "Philips" lighting. The combination of this sensory experience aims to engage the memory and emotions.</Text>
  </Description>
